         <abstract>
            <p>Let $x(p)$ be the point which minimizes the residual of a linear system in the $l_p$ norm. It is know that under certain conditions $x(p) \rightarrow x^\ast$, the Chebyshev or $l_\infty$ solution, as $p \rightarrow \infty$. A differential equation describing $x(p)$ is derived from which an iterative scheme is devised. A convergence analysis is given and numerical results are presented.</p>
          </abstract>
